Many, many years ago I was in the &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t want women/PoC/minorities quotas in Tech. That&rsquo;s not needed. After all, this is a meritocracy, so if you&rsquo;re good at programming that&rsquo;s all that counts&rdquo;.
Boy was I wrong&hellip;
It&rsquo;s a meritocracy if you don&rsquo;t feel attacked. If you feel safe. If you can be yourself. If you don&rsquo;t have to waste that much time/energy pretending to be a different person. If you don&rsquo;t hate going to the bathroom and finding someone else inside.
